# C++ Multi Line Comment
The C++ multi line comment is used to comment multiple lines of code. 
It is surrounded by slash and asterisk (/∗ ..... ∗/). 
Let's see an example of multi line comment in C++.



*********************************************************************************************


#include <ostream>  
using namespace std;  
int main()  
{  
/* declare and   
print variable in C++. */   
 int x = 35;     
 cout<<x<<"\n";         
}  


***************************************************************************************************************

Output:

35